            author: 'Priya Nair',
            date: 'March 13, 2026',
            readTime: '6 min read'
        }
    ],
    india: [
        {
            image: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1524492412937-b28074a5d7da',
            title: '🏗️ India\'s Infrastructure Boom',
            summary: 'Government announces 8 new expressways and 12 metro projects.',
            fullStory: 'Union Minister for Road Transport unveiled the "Bharat Connectivity Mission" worth ₹15 lakh crore. The projects include the Delhi-Mumbai Expressway extension, Chennai-Bengaluru Industrial Corridor, and metro expansions in 12 tier-2 cities. The initiative aims to create 5 million jobs and reduce logistics costs from 14% to 8% of GDP. Construction will utilize green technologies and recycled materials. Environmental impact assessments have been completed for all projects, with completion targets set for 2030.',
