            summary: 'UPI transactions cross 15 billion mark in February 2026.',
            fullStory: 'NPCI data reveals unprecedented growth in digital payments, with UPI recording 15.2 billion transactions worth ₹22 lakh crore. Rural adoption grew by 65% year-on-year, driven by feature phone-based UPI solutions. The government\'s "Digital Payment Incentive Scheme" has onboarded 50 million new users. International expansion continues with Nepal, Bhutan, and France adopting UPI. Cybersecurity measures have been strengthened with AI-based fraud detection systems handling 99.5% of suspicious transactions.',
